The maximum duration for which the computer can transmit at the full 10 Mbps is 1.6 seconds.

The token bucket is filled at a rate of 2 Mbps. It is initially filled to capacity with 16 Megabits.

The time it takes to fill the bucket is:

\begin{code}
16 Megabits / 2 Mbps = 8 seconds
\end{code}

The time it takes to drain the bucket is:

\begin{code}
10 Mbps / 2 Mbps = 5 seconds
\end{code}

The maximum duration for which the computer can transmit at the full 10 Mbps is:

\begin{code}
8 - 5 = 3 seconds
\end{code}

